Feature: Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime

  Background:
    Given the built unpacked extension has a typed compatibility project adopted through rendered migration controls
    And production capture callbacks and the visible Live validator are active
    And this feature proves evaluator integration rather than greenfield editor completeness

  # Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 001
  Scenario: Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 001
    When the operator compiles a project containing linked pages, events, applicability, flows, profiles, schemas, and assignments
    Then the visible compiler result names stable identities for every executable reference
    And a deliberately dangling step reference blocks compilation at that selector field

  # Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 002
  Scenario: Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 002
    Given the adopted project compiles to one executable plan
    When the operator opens the rendered compiler result
    Then candidate indexes, flow automata, effective schemas, and stable reference diagnostics are visible
    And the persisted plan names the adopted canonical revision and content identity

  # Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 003
  Scenario: Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 003
    Given the actual demo tab emitted an event through the page data layer
    When real Chrome messaging delivers it to the extension observer and Live validator
    Then the Live event row displays winner, flow step, effective schema, issues, and plan content identity from one evaluation
    And persisted runtime evidence references that result without becoming an input

  # Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 004
  Scenario: Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 004
    Given the adopted published release and its draft both compile
    When one draft matcher is changed without publication
    Then the rendered preview names the draft plan and Live names the unchanged published plan
    And a page-emitted event continues to use only the published routing and schema

  # Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 005
  Scenario: Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 005
    Given one page-emitted event produced a visible Live evaluation result
    When persisted routing evidence and runtime state are inspected read-only
    Then they name that result's stable IDs and content identity
    And deleting the evidence record does not change a repeated Live evaluation

  # Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 006
  Scenario: Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 006
    Given migration stages an invalid regular expression while Live uses the last valid plan
    When the operator reviews the staged matcher
    Then the exact expression field displays actionable syntax guidance
    And Live continues to name the unchanged published plan revision after a page-emitted event
    And the invalid stage cannot replace the valid plan

  # Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 007
  Scenario: Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 007
    Given Retail and Trade have the same source, event, URL, and markerless final payload
    When their distinct prior journeys emit events from the actual demo tab through real Chrome messaging
    Then the visible Live validator selects different assignment and schema IDs
    And neither result is an assignment tie or a routing-only record

  # Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 008
  Scenario: Data layer unified specification evaluation runtime 008
    Given a migrated project has not yet produced matching fixture and Live results
    When the operator opens the actual Builder and release review
    Then Preview and the parity failure are visible and every production Publish control is disabled
    When the operator repairs the project and the scenario-specific parity check passes
    Then Preview clears and release eligibility derives from the unified evaluator result
